28absl::optional<DataRate> OptionalRateFromOptionalBps(
29 absl::optional<int> bitrate_bps) {
30 if (bitrate_bps) {
31 return DataRate::BitsPerSec(*bitrate_bps);
32 } else {
33 return absl::nullopt;
34 }
35}
36} // namespace
37
38enum {
39 kTimestampGroupLengthMs = 5,
40 kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift = 8,
41 kInterArrivalShift = RTPHeaderExtension::kAbsSendTimeFraction +
42 kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift,
43 kInitialProbingIntervalMs = 2000,
44 kMinClusterSize = 4,
45 kMaxProbePackets = 15,
46 kExpectedNumberOfProbes = 3
47};
48
49static const double kTimestampToMs =
50 1000.0 / static_cast<double>(1 << kInterArrivalShift);
51
52template <typename K, typename V>
53std::vector<K> Keys(const std::map<K, V>& map) {
54 std::vector<K> keys;
55 keys.reserve(map.size());
56 for (typename std::map<K, V>::const_iterator it = map.begin();
57 it != map.end(); ++it) {
58 keys.push_back(it->first);
59 }
60 return keys;
61}
62
63uint32_t ConvertMsTo24Bits(int64_t time_ms) {
64 uint32_t time_24_bits =
65 static_cast<uint32_t>(((static_cast<uint64_t>(time_ms)
66 << RTPHeaderExtension::kAbsSendTimeFraction) +
67 500) /
68 1000) &
69 0x00FFFFFF;
70 return time_24_bits;
71}

73RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::~RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime() =
74 default;
75
76bool RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::IsWithinClusterBounds(
77 int send_delta_ms,
78 const Cluster& cluster_aggregate) {
79 if (cluster_aggregate.count == 0)
80 return true;
81 float cluster_mean = cluster_aggregate.send_mean_ms /
82 static_cast<float>(cluster_aggregate.count);
83 return fabs(static_cast<float>(send_delta_ms) - cluster_mean) < 2.5f;
84}
85
86void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::AddCluster(std::list<Cluster>* clusters,
87 Cluster* cluster) {
88 cluster->send_mean_ms /= static_cast<float>(cluster->count);
89 cluster->recv_mean_ms /= static_cast<float>(cluster->count);
90 cluster->mean_size /= cluster->count;
91 clusters->push_back(*cluster);
92}

94RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime(
95 RemoteBitrateObserver* observer,
96 Clock* clock)
97 : clock_(clock),
98 observer_(observer),
99 inter_arrival_(),
100 estimator_(),
101 detector_(&field_trials_),
102 incoming_bitrate_(kBitrateWindowMs, 8000),
103 incoming_bitrate_initialized_(false),
104 total_probes_received_(0),
105 first_packet_time_ms_(-1),
106 last_update_ms_(-1),
107 uma_recorded_(false),
108 remote_rate_(&field_trials_) {
109 RTC_DCHECK(clock_);
110 RTC_DCHECK(observer_);
111 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime: Instantiating.";
112}
113
114void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::ComputeClusters(
115 std::list<Cluster>* clusters) const {
116 Cluster current;
117 int64_t prev_send_time = -1;
118 int64_t prev_recv_time = -1;
119 for (std::list<Probe>::const_iterator it = probes_.begin();
120 it != probes_.end(); ++it) {
121 if (prev_send_time >= 0) {
122 int send_delta_ms = it->send_time_ms - prev_send_time;
123 int recv_delta_ms = it->recv_time_ms - prev_recv_time;
124 if (send_delta_ms >= 1 && recv_delta_ms >= 1) {
125 ++current.num_above_min_delta;
126 }
127 if (!IsWithinClusterBounds(send_delta_ms, current)) {
128 if (current.count >= kMinClusterSize && current.send_mean_ms > 0.0f &&
129 current.recv_mean_ms > 0.0f) {
130 AddCluster(clusters, &current);
131 }
132 current = Cluster();
133 }
134 current.send_mean_ms += send_delta_ms;
135 current.recv_mean_ms += recv_delta_ms;
136 current.mean_size += it->payload_size;
137 ++current.count;
138 }
139 prev_send_time = it->send_time_ms;
140 prev_recv_time = it->recv_time_ms;
141 }
142 if (current.count >= kMinClusterSize && current.send_mean_ms > 0.0f &&
143 current.recv_mean_ms > 0.0f) {
144 AddCluster(clusters, &current);
145 }
146}
147
148std::list<Cluster>::const_iterator
149RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::FindBestProbe(
150 const std::list<Cluster>& clusters) const {
151 int highest_probe_bitrate_bps = 0;
152 std::list<Cluster>::const_iterator best_it = clusters.end();
153 for (std::list<Cluster>::const_iterator it = clusters.begin();
154 it != clusters.end(); ++it) {
155 if (it->send_mean_ms == 0 || it->recv_mean_ms == 0)
156 continue;
157 if (it->num_above_min_delta > it->count / 2 &&
158 (it->recv_mean_ms - it->send_mean_ms <= 2.0f &&
159 it->send_mean_ms - it->recv_mean_ms <= 5.0f)) {
160 int probe_bitrate_bps =
161 std::min(it->GetSendBitrateBps(), it->GetRecvBitrateBps());
162 if (probe_bitrate_bps > highest_probe_bitrate_bps) {
163 highest_probe_bitrate_bps = probe_bitrate_bps;
164 best_it = it;
165 }
166 } else {
167 int send_bitrate_bps = it->mean_size * 8 * 1000 / it->send_mean_ms;
168 int recv_bitrate_bps = it->mean_size * 8 * 1000 / it->recv_mean_ms;
169 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Probe failed, sent at " << send_bitrate_bps
170 << " bps, received at " << recv_bitrate_bps
171 << " bps. Mean send delta: " << it->send_mean_ms
172 << " ms, mean recv delta: " << it->recv_mean_ms
173 << " ms, num probes: " << it->count;
174 break;
175 }
176 }
177 return best_it;
178}
179
180RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::ProbeResult
181RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::ProcessClusters(int64_t now_ms) {
182 std::list<Cluster> clusters;
183 ComputeClusters(&clusters);
184 if (clusters.empty()) {
185 // If we reach the max number of probe packets and still have no clusters,
186 // we will remove the oldest one.
187 if (probes_.size() >= kMaxProbePackets)
188 probes_.pop_front();
189 return ProbeResult::kNoUpdate;
190 }
191
192 std::list<Cluster>::const_iterator best_it = FindBestProbe(clusters);
193 if (best_it != clusters.end()) {
194 int probe_bitrate_bps =
195 std::min(best_it->GetSendBitrateBps(), best_it->GetRecvBitrateBps());
196 // Make sure that a probe sent on a lower bitrate than our estimate can't
197 // reduce the estimate.
198 if (IsBitrateImproving(probe_bitrate_bps)) {
199 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Probe successful, sent at "
200 << best_it->GetSendBitrateBps() << " bps, received at "
201 << best_it->GetRecvBitrateBps()
202 << " bps. Mean send delta: " << best_it->send_mean_ms
203 << " ms, mean recv delta: " << best_it->recv_mean_ms
204 << " ms, num probes: " << best_it->count;
205 remote_rate_.SetEstimate(DataRate::BitsPerSec(probe_bitrate_bps),
206 Timestamp::Millis(now_ms));
207 return ProbeResult::kBitrateUpdated;
208 }
209 }
210
211 // Not probing and received non-probe packet, or finished with current set
212 // of probes.
213 if (clusters.size() >= kExpectedNumberOfProbes)
214 probes_.clear();
215 return ProbeResult::kNoUpdate;
216}
217
218bool RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::IsBitrateImproving(
219 int new_bitrate_bps) const {
220 bool initial_probe = !remote_rate_.ValidEstimate() && new_bitrate_bps > 0;
221 bool bitrate_above_estimate =
222 remote_rate_.ValidEstimate() &&
223 new_bitrate_bps > remote_rate_.LatestEstimate().bps<int>();
224 return initial_probe || bitrate_above_estimate;
225}
226
227void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::IncomingPacket(
228 int64_t arrival_time_ms,
229 size_t payload_size,
230 const RTPHeader& header) {
231 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&network_race_);
232 if (!header.extension.hasAbsoluteSendTime) {
233 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
234 << "RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTimeImpl: Incoming packet "
235 "is missing absolute send time extension!";
236 return;
237 }
238 IncomingPacketInfo(arrival_time_ms, header.extension.absoluteSendTime,
239 payload_size, header.ssrc);
240}
241
242void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::IncomingPacketInfo(
243 int64_t arrival_time_ms,
244 uint32_t send_time_24bits,
245 size_t payload_size,
246 uint32_t ssrc) {
247 RTC_CHECK(send_time_24bits < (1ul << 24));
248 if (!uma_recorded_) {
249 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(kBweTypeHistogram, BweNames::kReceiverAbsSendTime,
250 BweNames::kBweNamesMax);
251 uma_recorded_ = true;
252 }
253 // Shift up send time to use the full 32 bits that inter_arrival works with,
254 // so wrapping works properly.
255 uint32_t timestamp = send_time_24bits << kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift;
256 int64_t send_time_ms = static_cast<int64_t>(timestamp) * kTimestampToMs;
257
258 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
259 // TODO(holmer): SSRCs are only needed for REMB, should be broken out from
260 // here.
261
262 // Check if incoming bitrate estimate is valid, and if it needs to be reset.
263 absl::optional<uint32_t> incoming_bitrate =
264 incoming_bitrate_.Rate(arrival_time_ms);
265 if (incoming_bitrate) {
266 incoming_bitrate_initialized_ = true;
267 } else if (incoming_bitrate_initialized_) {
268 // Incoming bitrate had a previous valid value, but now not enough data
269 // point are left within the current window. Reset incoming bitrate
270 // estimator so that the window size will only contain new data points.
271 incoming_bitrate_.Reset();
272 incoming_bitrate_initialized_ = false;
273 }
274 incoming_bitrate_.Update(payload_size, arrival_time_ms);
275
276 if (first_packet_time_ms_ == -1)
277 first_packet_time_ms_ = now_ms;
278
279 uint32_t ts_delta = 0;
280 int64_t t_delta = 0;
281 int size_delta = 0;
282 bool update_estimate = false;
283 uint32_t target_bitrate_bps = 0;
284 std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs;
285 {
286 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
287
288 TimeoutStreams(now_ms);
289 RTC_DCHECK(inter_arrival_.get());
290 RTC_DCHECK(estimator_.get());
291 ssrcs_[ssrc] = now_ms;
292
293 // For now only try to detect probes while we don't have a valid estimate.
294 // We currently assume that only packets larger than 200 bytes are paced by
295 // the sender.
296 const size_t kMinProbePacketSize = 200;
297 if (payload_size > kMinProbePacketSize &&
298 (!remote_rate_.ValidEstimate() ||
299 now_ms - first_packet_time_ms_ < kInitialProbingIntervalMs)) {
300 // TODO(holmer): Use a map instead to get correct order?
301 if (total_probes_received_ < kMaxProbePackets) {
302 int send_delta_ms = -1;
303 int recv_delta_ms = -1;
304 if (!probes_.empty()) {
305 send_delta_ms = send_time_ms - probes_.back().send_time_ms;
306 recv_delta_ms = arrival_time_ms - probes_.back().recv_time_ms;
307 }
308 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Probe packet received: send time=" << send_time_ms
309 << " ms, recv time=" << arrival_time_ms
310 << " ms, send delta=" << send_delta_ms
311 << " ms, recv delta=" << recv_delta_ms << " ms.";
312 }
313 probes_.push_back(Probe(send_time_ms, arrival_time_ms, payload_size));
314 ++total_probes_received_;
315 // Make sure that a probe which updated the bitrate immediately has an
316 // effect by calling the OnReceiveBitrateChanged callback.
317 if (ProcessClusters(now_ms) == ProbeResult::kBitrateUpdated)
318 update_estimate = true;
319 }
320 if (inter_arrival_->ComputeDeltas(timestamp, arrival_time_ms, now_ms,
321 payload_size, &ts_delta, &t_delta,
322 &size_delta)) {
323 double ts_delta_ms = (1000.0 * ts_delta) / (1 << kInterArrivalShift);
324 estimator_->Update(t_delta, ts_delta_ms, size_delta, detector_.State(),
325 arrival_time_ms);
326 detector_.Detect(estimator_->offset(), ts_delta_ms,
327 estimator_->num_of_deltas(), arrival_time_ms);
328 }
329
330 if (!update_estimate) {
331 // Check if it's time for a periodic update or if we should update because
332 // of an over-use.
333 if (last_update_ms_ == -1 ||
334 now_ms - last_update_ms_ > remote_rate_.GetFeedbackInterval().ms()) {
335 update_estimate = true;
336 } else if (detector_.State() == BandwidthUsage::kBwOverusing) {
337 absl::optional<uint32_t> incoming_rate =
338 incoming_bitrate_.Rate(arrival_time_ms);
339 if (incoming_rate && remote_rate_.TimeToReduceFurther(
340 Timestamp::Millis(now_ms),
341 DataRate::BitsPerSec(*incoming_rate))) {
342 update_estimate = true;
343 }
344 }
345 }
346
347 if (update_estimate) {
348 // The first overuse should immediately trigger a new estimate.
349 // We also have to update the estimate immediately if we are overusing
350 // and the target bitrate is too high compared to what we are receiving.
351 const RateControlInput input(
352 detector_.State(),
353 OptionalRateFromOptionalBps(incoming_bitrate_.Rate(arrival_time_ms)));
354 target_bitrate_bps =
355 remote_rate_.Update(&input, Timestamp::Millis(now_ms))
356 .bps<uint32_t>();
357 update_estimate = remote_rate_.ValidEstimate();
358 ssrcs = Keys(ssrcs_);
359 }
360 }
361 if (update_estimate) {
362 last_update_ms_ = now_ms;
363 observer_->OnReceiveBitrateChanged(ssrcs, target_bitrate_bps);
364 }
365}

367void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::Process() {}
368
369int64_t RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::TimeUntilNextProcess() {
370 const int64_t kDisabledModuleTime = 1000;
371 return kDisabledModuleTime;
372}
373
374void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::TimeoutStreams(int64_t now_ms) {
375 for (Ssrcs::iterator it = ssrcs_.begin(); it != ssrcs_.end();) {
376 if ((now_ms - it->second) > kStreamTimeOutMs) {
377 ssrcs_.erase(it++);
378 } else {
379 ++it;
380 }
381 }
382 if (ssrcs_.empty()) {
383 // We can't update the estimate if we don't have any active streams.
384 inter_arrival_.reset(
385 new InterArrival((kTimestampGroupLengthMs << kInterArrivalShift) / 1000,
386 kTimestampToMs, true));
387 estimator_.reset(new OveruseEstimator(OverUseDetectorOptions()));
388 // We deliberately don't reset the first_packet_time_ms_ here for now since
389 // we only probe for bandwidth in the beginning of a call right now.
390 }
391}

393void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::OnRttUpdate(int64_t avg_rtt_ms,
394 int64_t max_rtt_ms) {
395 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
396 remote_rate_.SetRtt(TimeDelta::Millis(avg_rtt_ms));
397}
398
399void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::RemoveStream(uint32_t ssrc) {
400 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
401 ssrcs_.erase(ssrc);
402}
403
404bool RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::LatestEstimate(
405 std::vector<uint32_t>* ssrcs,
406 uint32_t* bitrate_bps) const {
407 // Currently accessed from both the process thread (see
408 // ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::Process()) and the configuration thread (see
409 // Call::GetStats()). Should in the future only be accessed from a single
410 // thread.
411 RTC_DCHECK(ssrcs);
412 RTC_DCHECK(bitrate_bps);
413 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
414 if (!remote_rate_.ValidEstimate()) {
415 return false;
416 }
417 *ssrcs = Keys(ssrcs_);
418 if (ssrcs_.empty()) {
419 *bitrate_bps = 0;
420 } else {
421 *bitrate_bps = remote_rate_.LatestEstimate().bps<uint32_t>();
422 }
423 return true;
424}
425
426void RemoteBitrateEstimatorAbsSendTime::SetMinBitrate(int min_bitrate_bps) {
427 // Called from both the configuration thread and the network thread. Shouldn't
428 // be called from the network thread in the future.
429 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
430 remote_rate_.SetMinBitrate(DataRate::BitsPerSec(min_bitrate_bps));
431}
